  {
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think I know what bugs me about this PR. While I do agree with you we should fix it at the source, I think this should be at the helper level.\nIndeed, in the helper:\n- `addNumericRefinement(attribute, operator, value)` type-checks value and convert it to a float if it's a string\n- but `removeNumericRefinement(attribute, operator, value)` just does a simple `===` comparison\n\nWhich means that:\n\n``` js\nvar val = /* ... */;\nhelper.addNumericRefinement('attribute', '=', val);\nhelper.removeNumericRefinement('attribute', '=', val);\n```\n\nis actually not guaranteed to work, which is, to me, weird.\n\nBy fixing this, we would actually fix the need for this PR.\n",
